    "updated_at": "2013-12-19T03:48:59Z",
    "body": "The low-level condition variables and mutexes should really be different types because the need to have multiple condition variables for a single mutex is really common.\n\nC++11 provides overloads of the condition variable wait methods taking a predicate function, so the `while` loop is internal to the method.\n\nhttp://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/thread/condition_variable\n",
